   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note class="- topic/note ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The AGV has two travel modes</p>
            </note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "/>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Manual mode is mainly used for setup and troubleshooting. In manual operation,
                     the AGV is controlled via a wired remote control. The trained operator is
                     responsible for the travel. Travel can take place with or without load.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">In automatic operation, the AGV receives its travel orders from a master
                     computer (travel to position X, fetch load Y, and bring it to position Z),
                     which are processed along the specified route. In automatic mode, the AGV can
                     travel both with and without a load.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">There is also a semi-automatic mode that allows the operator to specify the
                     AGV target position.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The control screen and the main power switch are located on the AGV.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Use this power switch to turn the AGV on or off.</p>
               </note>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">This switch must always be in the "O" position during maintenance work.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Follow plant lockout-tagout procedures.</li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If any <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">E-Stop</b> in the SBS system is pressed, the AGV and the rest of the
                     system will stop.</p>
               </note>
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The operator can use the SBS screens to stop operation, in which case the AGV
                     completes its current order before stopping.</p>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The main screen is shown on the right. To display the main screen when another
               screen is showing, click the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Home</uicontrol>button in the lower left
               corner of the screen.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The following information is displayed:</p>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Current load</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Current job</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Current origin and target position</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Status of battery, drives, temperature, network, WLAN</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">OnTrack, MasterLinkUp (connection to Kollmorgen PC) </li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The top section of the main screen displays:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Name of the AGV (on the left)</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Battery charge state, shown with a battery and percent charge.  A lightning symbol appears if the AGV is currently charging.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Stop symbol, which appears only when the vehicle has been stopped by the controller. (The reason for the stop is listed on the detail screen.)</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">HEGLA logo</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Use the buttons on the bottom of the screen to navigate between the various operating screens.  From left to right, the buttons are:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Back to Main Screen/Menu</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Manual Operation</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Carriage Details</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Battery</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Information Details</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Maintenance</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">User </li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Status Indicators are displayed using four colors in the top right box, behind the
               images:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Green = All OK</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Yellow = Warning</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Red = Error alarm</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Purple = Serious error (prevents movement of the AGV)</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Messages are also provided in four colors to indicate the type of message.  They are displayed on the alarm screen (3rd screen from left of the user log in button). </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Black = Message</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Yellow = Warning</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Red = Error alarm</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Purple = Serious error that prevents movement of the AGV </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The last active fault messages are displayed with "Alarm‚Äù on the Information
                     Details screen on the AGV, and usually on the top of the screen.</p>
               </note>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
